body:
@snicoll Thanks for raising this issue! I think the original intention was to signal that users should choose a version of `junit:junit` >= 4.12. While the 4.13 release will come of soonish, we won't upgrade the dependency version in junit-vintage-engine but users can choose a to use the newer version.

Regarding Gradle, you shouldn't add junit-vintage-engine as a `testCompile` dependency, it should really be `testRuntimeOnly`. Thus, you'll have to add `junit:junit` yourself anyway.

That being said I think it would be more consistent and also more correct conceptually to use `compile` scope for `junit:junit` in `junit-vintage-engine`. I'll change that.
